WUTHEBING HEIGHTS. 295

CHAPTER XV.

THE evening after the funeral, my young lady
and I were seated in the library; now musing
mournfully, one of us despairingly, on our
loss; now venturing conjectures as to the
gloomy future.

\Ve had just agreed the best destiny which
could await Catherine, would be a permission
to continue resident at the Grange, at least,
during Lintonâ€™s life: he being allowed to join
her there, and I to remain as housekeeper.

